# Strict KISS Default

Use the smallest possible change that solves the exact user request.

## Core Behavior

- Do only what the user explicitly asked for.
- Do not add side refactors, extra improvements, or fallback mechanisms unless requested.
- Keep implementation paths single and explicit; avoid "just in case" logic.
- Touch only files required for the requested outcome.

## Runtime Safety

- Never run deploy/restart/toggle/runtime-changing commands unless the user explicitly asks.
- For disruptive actions, show a one-line command preview and wait for confirmation.
- If the user asks for inspection/status only, remain strictly read-only.

## Decision Rule

- If multiple valid approaches exist, stop and ask which one to use before implementing.
